      "short": "",
      "value": "<p>The creature does not use any visual senses and is thus never subject to any effect that requires the creature to see a target or effect. Sightless creatures normally have some form of @Compendium[sfrpg.universal-creature-rules.4HvnYWLhFBiuvDxD]{Blindsight} to compensate for their sightlessness, but if not, they are assumed to be able to operate as well as a creature with normal vision unless the creature&rsquo;s description says otherwise.</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListRulesAll_ctl48_LabelName\"><em>Format</em>: <strong>Senses</strong> sightless</span></p>",
